cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the synthesis problem for LTL properties of timed automata, which involves logical reasoning.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a symbolic zone-based method for solving the parameter synthesis problem, which involves programming language concepts.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated synthesis of parameter valuations for timed automata, which is a problem in AI.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with timed automata, which are a type of formal language and automata.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also relevant as timed automata are used to model and analyze real-time systems, which is a topic in systems and control.
